229
00:09:47,410 --> 00:09:48,690
There's got to be a way somehow!

230
00:09:48,691 --> 00:09:51,970
How did the original Digi-Destined kids
defeat this enemy?

231
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:56,870
I'll take these children and use their
fear to make them digital and disappear!

232
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:07,070
What's this?

233
00:10:07,290 --> 00:10:07,850
Fascinating!

234
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:11,430
Our bodies are being broken down into
little bits of digital information!

235
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:11,950
Fascinating!

236
00:10:12,490 --> 00:10:13,690
Let's stay calm, everyone!

237
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:14,910
Don't fall to pieces!

238
00:10:15,170 --> 00:10:16,170
Too late!

239
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:31,140
Where are we?

240
00:10:31,260 --> 00:10:32,440
We're information now!

241
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,700
This is where all digital information
gathers!

242
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:35,940
It's the world of data!

243
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:36,640
Data?

244
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,160
I'm too young to be dating!

245
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,500
It's not the same.

246
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:42,020
Sometimes too much information's a bad
thing.

247
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:43,420
Can we get back?

248
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:44,700
I don't know, Kari.

249
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,660
Nothing like this has ever happened to us
before.

250
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,760
I don't know what to do.

251
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:48,580
Is this it?

252
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:49,500
Have we lost?

253
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,240
I'd say that's a pretty good conclusion.

254
00:10:51,241 --> 00:10:52,360
Come on, you guys!

255
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,100
Don't quit now!

256
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:53,840
Why not?

257
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:57,440
Look, we can't stop fighting now just
because of a little setback.

258
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,200
So what with bits of information?

259
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:01,476
We have no tags and
crests, we can't digivolve, and

260
00:11:01,477 --> 00:11:03,760
we're facing the most
powerful enemy of all time.

261
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,180
I don't see what the problem is.

262
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:05,960
Listen, Biomon.

263
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,360
You guys have a great attitude about this
whole thing.

264
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:10,905
But all the positive thinking
in the world can't guarantee

265
00:11:10,906 --> 00:11:13,160
